1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:01,400
[GRUNTS]

2
00:00:02,900 --> 00:00:04,400
<i> Jade.</i> [GRUNTS]

3
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:07,400
<i> Jade.</i>

4
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:08,533
[SOBS]

5
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,900
<i> I'm so sorry I was too late.</i>

6
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:14,300
<i>Mom, it's not your fault.
Okay?</i>

7
00:00:15,267 --> 00:00:17,733
<i>Michael Fernandez's sons
need help.</i>

8
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:19,233
<i> They were attacked.</i>

9
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:21,067
<i>- Gio!
- Don't let go!</i>

10
00:00:21,167 --> 00:00:22,700
<i> Hold on, please!</i>

11
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,300
<i>Nurse,
please save my brother!</i>

12
00:00:25,433 --> 00:00:27,300
<i>- We need to check you.
- No!</i>

13
00:00:27,433 --> 00:00:30,367
<i>Prioritize our brother.
His condition is critical.</i>

14
00:00:30,467 --> 00:00:32,700
<i>What do we do, Martin?
Bok will come after us.</i>

15
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,600
<i>No. The police are
looking for him, okay?</i>

16
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:36,167
<i> Even his accomplices.</i>

17
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:40,500
<i> Bok?</i>

18
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:45,733
[HOTEL STAFF]
<i> You're not coming, sir?</i>

19
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:47,333
Yes.

20
00:00:47,467 --> 00:00:48,733
Just tell them.

21
00:00:50,833 --> 00:00:53,067
[UTENSILS CLINKING]

22
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:56,167
[ROI] I didn't kill them!

23
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:58,900
<i> I didn't kill Michael!</i>

24
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:01,933
<i> And I didn't kill Federico!</i>

25
00:01:02,100 --> 00:01:04,267
<i>They were already dead
when I found them!</i>

26
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:10,233
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

27
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:12,800
I'm glad you're going
back to the office, Leon.

28
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,600
You know...

29
00:01:16,733 --> 00:01:21,333
Dad wouldn't be happy if
you neglected his businesses.

30
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:24,167
I want to make sure
you and Mom are okay

31
00:01:24,300 --> 00:01:25,700
before I go back
to work on-site.

32
00:01:25,833 --> 00:01:26,967
Thank you, Leon.

33
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:32,867
I already prepared
Mom's stuff for Spain, Leon.

34
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,700
[JOSH]
Even though I'll miss Mom...

35
00:01:35,833 --> 00:01:37,700
I agree that
she should stay there,

36
00:01:37,833 --> 00:01:40,000
especially after what happened.

37
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:45,033
What if...

38
00:01:45,167 --> 00:01:46,867
I go with her?

39
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:47,633
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

40
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:49,167
That won't be necessary,
Justin.

41
00:01:49,433 --> 00:01:51,833
Aunt Yayo will keep
Mom company.

42
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,300
[LEON] Mom's better off
with Aunt Yayo.

43
00:01:54,433 --> 00:01:56,367
If one of us went with her,

44
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,633
she wouldn't be able to rest

45
00:01:57,767 --> 00:01:59,700
because she would be
taking care of us.

46
00:01:59,833 --> 00:02:01,333
So, this is it?

47
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:02,667
Life goes on for Mom.

48
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:04,000
Everything's back to normal?

49
00:02:04,167 --> 00:02:05,133
No.

50
00:02:05,233 --> 00:02:11,000
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

51
00:02:11,167 --> 00:02:13,400
Is there something wrong,
Leon?

52
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:15,600
Uh...

53
00:02:15,733 --> 00:02:16,500
No.

54
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:18,200
Nothing's wrong.

55
00:02:18,367 --> 00:02:19,667
But I think

56
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:22,500
we should talk to
Martin and his brothers.

57
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:25,567
Something bad
happened to them too.

58
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:27,100
We need to
check on them also.

59
00:02:27,233 --> 00:02:34,167
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:45,833
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:03:39,267 --> 00:03:40,800
That's all, sir.

62
00:03:41,767 --> 00:03:43,567
Thank you
for your cooperation.

63
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:45,933
Good thing
you can go home now.

64
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:48,900
Sir, has Bok been found?

65
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,067
Did you catch him?

66
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:54,733
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

67
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:56,167
Yes.

68
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:57,800
Including his accomplices.

69
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:01,767
But Bok is dead already.

70
00:04:03,633 --> 00:04:04,633
[MARTIN] Dead?

71
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,833
How? Did he fight back?

72
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:10,633
We found him
in the location you provided.

73
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,200
He tried to escape,

74
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,333
but by the time we found him,

75
00:04:14,467 --> 00:04:15,767
he was already dead.

76
00:04:16,567 --> 00:04:18,267
Jeez.

77
00:04:19,333 --> 00:04:21,433
All we wanted was for him to
stay away from Gio,

78
00:04:21,567 --> 00:04:22,800
not for him to die.

79
00:04:22,967 --> 00:04:29,933
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

80
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:42,500
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

81
00:04:57,567 --> 00:05:03,133
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

82
00:05:03,267 --> 00:05:04,900
[TAPPING]

83
00:05:11,233 --> 00:05:18,067
[STIRRING MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

84
00:05:31,067 --> 00:05:32,733
[LAPTOP WHIRS]

85
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,100
[CLACKS]

86
00:05:43,233 --> 00:05:49,533
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

87
00:05:49,633 --> 00:05:50,867
[BEEP]

88
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:59,967
[CLACKING CONTINUES]

89
00:06:00,100 --> 00:06:01,067
[BEEP]

90
00:06:03,667 --> 00:06:04,733
[LEON] Jade's birthday?

91
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:08,467
[CLACKING CONTINUES]

92
00:06:08,633 --> 00:06:09,567
[CHIMES]

93
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:16,667
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

94
00:06:21,767 --> 00:06:23,400
[LEON]<i> Dad dealt with
</i> a lot of people

95
00:06:23,533 --> 00:06:25,133
<i> in his business transactions.</i>

96
00:06:26,967 --> 00:06:29,667
<i>Which one of them has  motive
to kill him and Uncle Mike?</i>

97
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:36,800
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

98
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,167
[CLACKS]

99
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:43,133
"Dear Mr. Almazan,

100
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,633
Thank you for your payment
of 322,475.01..."

101
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:46,767
[LEON]<i> This was just
</i> a few days before he died.

102
00:06:47,633 --> 00:06:50,000
<i>But no package for him
was delivered.</i>

103
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:53,367
What is this expensive purchase?

104
00:06:57,633 --> 00:06:58,700
[CAMERA CLICKS]

105
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,300
[DOOR OPENS, SLAMS]

106
00:07:01,467 --> 00:07:02,367
[JUSTIN] Leon?

107
00:07:03,467 --> 00:07:04,700
What are you doing here?

108
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:07,667
I'm just checking some
of Dad's transactions.

109
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:10,033
- I can help you find it.
- No.

110
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,367
I've found it.

111
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,300
Do you need anything?

112
00:07:15,533 --> 00:07:16,867
Ah, no.

113
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,633
Luna's looking for you.
It's time to eat.

114
00:07:19,733 --> 00:07:21,133
I'm not eating.

115
00:07:21,267 --> 00:07:22,300
I'm leaving.

116
00:07:22,433 --> 00:07:23,867
I have something
to take care of.

117
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,400
- At the hotel? Because--
- No.

118
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:27,467
At the office.

119
00:07:29,167 --> 00:07:30,300
At Dad's office?

120
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:32,200
Yes.

121
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:34,733
There's an emergency.

122
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:36,967
So I have to leave.

123
00:07:37,067 --> 00:07:39,467
Could you give me a ride?
I don't want to eat lunch here.

124
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:40,800
No.

125
00:07:41,533 --> 00:07:42,733
I mean...

126
00:07:43,567 --> 00:07:45,233
Luna cooked lunch already.

127
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:49,300
Eat here so her
efforts don't go to waste.

128
00:07:49,433 --> 00:07:56,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

129
00:07:57,867 --> 00:07:59,933
[JUSTIN]<i> Why do you have
</i> Dad's laptop, Leon?

130
00:08:00,067 --> 00:08:04,000
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

131
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:07,700
- [RAPHIE] Hello, Philippines!
- [SARI] And hello world!

132
00:08:07,867 --> 00:08:09,700
[CHESKA] Welcome to Hotel 88!

133
00:08:09,867 --> 00:08:11,433
[RAPHIE] The hotel
that's waiting...

134
00:08:11,567 --> 00:08:13,700
...for Gio who has returned!

135
00:08:13,867 --> 00:08:15,667
- Yeah!
- Welcome back, Sir Gio!

136
00:08:15,767 --> 00:08:17,533
- Welcome, Sir Gio!
- Ah!

137
00:08:17,633 --> 00:08:19,867
- [TRIXIE] Welcome back!
- [CHESKA] Oh!

138
00:08:20,067 --> 00:08:22,867
[TRIXIE] I'm sorry, this is all
I could make.

139
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:26,200
Welcome back
to my brother's brother!

140
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:27,200
[TRIXIE CHUCKLES]

141
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:28,767
[MONETTE] Come, let's stay
where you're safe,

142
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:31,133
and away
from a dangerous life!

143
00:08:31,267 --> 00:08:32,733
[CHESKA CHUCKLES]

144
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:34,933
Thank you.
Thank you to all of you.

145
00:08:35,067 --> 00:08:37,133
[RAPHIE] Aww, let's go, sir!

146
00:08:37,300 --> 00:08:40,933
[MONETTE] And, since the
brothers are complete again...

147
00:08:41,067 --> 00:08:42,700
Dinner will be special!

148
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:46,600
[ALL] Yay!

149
00:08:46,733 --> 00:08:50,033
[RAPHIE] My sister's so great!
Come on!

150
00:08:52,133 --> 00:08:54,267
[SARI] Sir, welcome back
as well.

151
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,467
Sari, I'm not the one
you should be welcoming back.

152
00:08:57,600 --> 00:09:01,333
Sir, I welcome you into my life
every single day.

153
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:05,300
That's my job
as your one and only assistant.

154
00:09:05,433 --> 00:09:07,100
Your one and only assistant.

155
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,100
Sari.

156
00:09:09,133 --> 00:09:11,100
I want to tell you something.

157
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:13,800
Then just say it, Sari.

158
00:09:15,867 --> 00:09:17,433
I just wanted to say that...

159
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:23,067
If Sir Gio returned today,
tomorrow, it'll be Ma'am Luna.

160
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:26,067
She called to say
she'll return tomorrow.

161
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:28,333
- I thought it's something else.
- That's all, sir!

162
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,367
You're going back to Manila?

163
00:09:38,467 --> 00:09:40,033
Is there an emergency
with your grandmother?

164
00:09:42,733 --> 00:09:44,200
Grandma's fine.

165
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:47,700
I just feel like I have
no more reason to stay here.

166
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:49,367
What do you mean no reason?

167
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,867
You are a part of this hotel.
You are one of the owners.

168
00:09:53,033 --> 00:09:55,500
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

169
00:09:55,633 --> 00:09:56,833
A co-owner who brought trouble.

170
00:10:01,933 --> 00:10:03,333
I know how Bok thinks.

171
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:07,300
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

172
00:10:07,433 --> 00:10:09,900
I should've known he was
going to cause trouble here.

173
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,833
You shouldn't have
been involved.

174
00:10:13,933 --> 00:10:15,400
If we really didn't want
to get involved,

175
00:10:15,567 --> 00:10:18,067
then we should've left you
right when he was chasing you.

176
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:21,500
Or we should've made you leave
during the music fest.

177
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:23,467
[KIKO] But we didn't.

178
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:26,133
Because we want you here.

179
00:10:26,267 --> 00:10:28,133
No matter if there's chaos
or not.

180
00:10:28,267 --> 00:10:29,733
[MARTIN] If you're worried
about your grandma,

181
00:10:29,867 --> 00:10:31,867
you can just bring her here.

182
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,733
Or I can arrange something
in Manila,

183
00:10:33,867 --> 00:10:35,333
so that someone can look
after her.

184
00:10:36,733 --> 00:10:38,433
Didn't I tell you
from the beginning?

185
00:10:38,567 --> 00:10:40,400
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

186
00:10:40,533 --> 00:10:42,433
I needed the money,
that's why I went here.

187
00:10:43,533 --> 00:10:44,600
But Bok's gone now.

188
00:10:45,533 --> 00:10:46,933
I don't owe a debt anymore,
I shouldn't--

189
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:48,100
[KIKO] What about us?

190
00:10:48,233 --> 00:10:50,933
Can't we be a reason
for you not to leave?

191
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:54,433
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

192
00:10:54,567 --> 00:10:57,167
I don't want you to get
in trouble because of me.

193
00:10:57,300 --> 00:10:59,033
Are we really going
to separate now?

194
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:02,100
After everything
that has happened?

195
00:11:02,233 --> 00:11:04,933
No one is leaving this family.

196
00:11:05,067 --> 00:11:07,167
[KIKO SCOFFS] Unfortunately,
we're your brothers.

197
00:11:08,133 --> 00:11:10,300
We won't let you
out of our lives.

198
00:11:10,433 --> 00:11:13,300
And this?
I'll bring this to my room.

199
00:11:13,467 --> 00:11:15,467
Or maybe I should put all
of your things there,

200
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:16,967
so you won't leave.

201
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:22,300
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

202
00:11:22,467 --> 00:11:29,300
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

203
00:11:31,767 --> 00:11:34,033
I want to know the truth.

204
00:11:34,167 --> 00:11:39,633
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

205
00:11:39,767 --> 00:11:41,100
I told you, didn't I?

206
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,933
Yes, I did kidnap Jade.

207
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:46,900
I'm not denying that.

208
00:11:47,033 --> 00:11:50,767
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

209
00:11:50,867 --> 00:11:52,167
But no matter what you do,

210
00:11:52,300 --> 00:11:55,400
you can't accuse me
for your father's death.

211
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:02,267
If you didn't kill them,
then what do you know?

212
00:12:03,767 --> 00:12:05,400
What did you see?

213
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:12,067
- [SLAMS]
- For God's sake, Roi!

214
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:19,233
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

215
00:12:20,733 --> 00:12:21,800
Yes, I was there.

216
00:12:22,567 --> 00:12:24,533
I was at the place
where sir died.

217
00:12:24,667 --> 00:12:29,500
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:12:29,633 --> 00:12:31,300
I accompanied Frida.

219
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:34,533
[FRIDA]<i> Roi, hurry up.
</i> We need to catch them.

220
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,200
<i> Yes, ma'am.</i>

221
00:12:39,067 --> 00:12:41,700
[ROI] Ma'am, the road ends here.

222
00:12:41,833 --> 00:12:43,267
<i> Ma'am! Wait, ma'am!</i>

223
00:12:44,067 --> 00:12:46,033
<i>- Fred!
- [ROI] Ma'am!</i>

224
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,833
<i> Fred!</i> [BREATHING RAPIDLY]

225
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,900
<i>- Fred! Roi!
- [ROI] Ma'am!</i>

226
00:12:50,067 --> 00:12:51,333
<i>Ma'am, you should return
to the hotel.</i>

227
00:12:51,433 --> 00:12:54,467
<i>I'll take care of this.
Your kids are waiting for you.</i>

228
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:57,467
<i>Promise me, Roi,
you'll bring home Fred and Mike.</i>

229
00:12:59,267 --> 00:13:01,067
[ROI] Frida is important to m.

230
00:13:02,100 --> 00:13:03,467
I don't want her hurt.

231
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:07,467
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

232
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:10,367
That's why I'm the one
who went looking for them.

233
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:14,067
<i>I have nothing
to do with it!</i>

234
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,400
[FEDERICO]<i> What do you mean
</i> nothing?!

235
00:13:15,567 --> 00:13:16,400
<i> You know that...</i>

236
00:13:16,567 --> 00:13:18,200
[ROI] I could hear them.

237
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:20,067
[MICHAEL]<i> He just wanted me
</i> to be his business partner!

238
00:13:20,233 --> 00:13:21,400
[ROI] I was close.

239
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:22,867
[MICHAEL]<i> But I didn't
</i> accept it!

240
00:13:23,633 --> 00:13:25,433
[ROI] But I was distracted
for just a while...

241
00:13:26,533 --> 00:13:27,400
when...

242
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:29,333
Bang!

243
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:32,167
A gun went off.

244
00:13:35,233 --> 00:13:36,767
[ROI] And when I looked
at them...

245
00:13:39,433 --> 00:13:41,433
They were already dead
on the ground.

246
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:42,600
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

247
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:47,567
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

248
00:13:51,867 --> 00:13:52,767
[GULPS]

249
00:13:57,133 --> 00:13:58,733
Who shot them?

250
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:06,133
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

251
00:14:06,267 --> 00:14:07,733
I don't know, Leon.

252
00:14:07,833 --> 00:14:09,900
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

253
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,600
I don't know.

254
00:14:11,733 --> 00:14:13,467
But I'm sure...

255
00:14:13,633 --> 00:14:14,633
It's not me.

256
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:18,467
[HANDCUFFS CLANGING]

257
00:14:19,333 --> 00:14:20,633
They didn't kill each other.

258
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:25,867
There was someone else.

259
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:33,033
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

260
00:14:36,433 --> 00:14:38,933
[LAUGHING MANIACALLY]

261
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:41,333
What's so funny? Huh?

262
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:46,100
There's someone else.
No...

263
00:14:46,267 --> 00:14:47,767
I just realized something.

264
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:51,833
How easy it is for you...

265
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:54,967
to pin your father's death
on me.

266
00:14:55,133 --> 00:14:56,733
Because you're the only one
with a motive.

267
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:58,800
If I wanted your father dead,

268
00:14:58,967 --> 00:15:00,467
I would've done it
a long time ago!

269
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:04,833
So I could've had Frida
all to myself.

270
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:08,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

271
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:12,933
Your mother is miserable
because of her husband.

272
00:15:15,867 --> 00:15:17,667
And I'm the only one, Leon...

273
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:19,100
[HANDCUFFS RATTLE]

274
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:23,000
I'm the only one
who can make her happy.

275
00:15:24,367 --> 00:15:26,700
But you ruined it.

276
00:15:26,867 --> 00:15:29,000
You ruined everything!

277
00:15:32,633 --> 00:15:35,933
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

278
00:15:38,733 --> 00:15:40,367
I love Frida.

279
00:15:41,833 --> 00:15:43,533
- I love her so much--
- [SLAMS TABLE]

280
00:15:43,667 --> 00:15:45,200
[LEON]
You've really lost it.

281
00:15:47,567 --> 00:15:49,467
Four times.

282
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:54,200
I heard the gun go off
four times.

283
00:15:56,067 --> 00:15:58,633
But what does
the police report say?

284
00:15:58,733 --> 00:16:00,033
Just two?

285
00:16:01,900 --> 00:16:03,233
That's not true.

286
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:07,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

287
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:09,800
I heard it clearly.

288
00:16:10,767 --> 00:16:11,933
Four.

289
00:16:12,100 --> 00:16:16,400
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

290
00:16:16,533 --> 00:16:17,867
Bang! Bang!

291
00:16:18,933 --> 00:16:21,033
Bang! Bang!

292
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:26,067
They altered
the police report.

293
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:30,767
Four.
So don't trust them.

294
00:16:32,433 --> 00:16:33,333
[INHALES SHARPLY]

295
00:16:33,467 --> 00:16:39,400
And if you think
that locking me up in here...

296
00:16:39,567 --> 00:16:42,900
means you've given justice
for your father's death,

297
00:16:45,567 --> 00:16:47,133
you're wrong.

298
00:16:48,133 --> 00:16:50,267
Because the real killer...

299
00:16:51,633 --> 00:16:53,767
is still out there.

300
00:16:53,933 --> 00:17:00,933
[MUSIC BECOMES GRIM]

301
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:25,400
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

302
00:17:30,633 --> 00:17:31,633
[FEDERICO] Leon.

303
00:17:32,667 --> 00:17:34,667
<i> Please remember...</i>

304
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:36,500
<i> This never happened.</i>

305
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,967
<i>Okay?
This never happened.</i>

306
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:47,000
- [ENGINE REVVING]
- [MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

307
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,633
[PHONE CHIMES]

308
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:58,633
<i>Where are you?
I'm already here at Hotel 88.</i>

309
00:18:03,067 --> 00:18:05,700
[ENGINE REVVING]

310
00:18:05,867 --> 00:18:12,633
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

311
00:18:15,367 --> 00:18:21,767
- [GRUNTING]
- [GROANING]

312
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:23,667
- [BLADE STRIKES]
- [YELLS IN PAIN]

313
00:18:23,767 --> 00:18:26,000
- [BLOWS LAND]
- [GROANING]

314
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:27,633
[KICK LANDS]

315
00:18:27,733 --> 00:18:29,133
<i> Dad?</i>

316
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:36,000
[GROANING]

317
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:41,333
[GROANING CONTINUES]

318
00:18:42,933 --> 00:18:44,800
[HANDBRAKE CLICKS]

319
00:18:44,900 --> 00:18:47,567
[ENGINE REVVING]

320
00:18:50,667 --> 00:18:51,867
[BODY SLAMS INTO CAR]

321
00:18:52,033 --> 00:18:53,733
[TIRES SCREECH]

322
00:18:53,900 --> 00:19:00,667
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

323
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:22,867
<i> Dad?</i>

324
00:19:22,967 --> 00:19:24,100
<i> Who was that?</i>

325
00:19:24,267 --> 00:19:26,567
<i>Son.
You need to leave, please.</i>

326
00:19:28,467 --> 00:19:29,600
<i> Uncle Mike?</i>

327
00:19:34,433 --> 00:19:36,267
<i>He's dead.
He's dead, Dad.</i>

328
00:19:36,433 --> 00:19:37,967
<i>- He's dead, Dad.
- Leon.</i>

329
00:19:38,133 --> 00:19:40,433
<i>- Leon. Leon.
- He's dead, Dad. He's dead.</i>

330
00:19:40,567 --> 00:19:41,867
<i> You have to go.</i>

331
00:19:41,967 --> 00:19:43,767
<i> Come on. Please?</i>

332
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:45,433
<i>- Come on, Dad. Let's go!
- No.</i>

333
00:19:45,567 --> 00:19:47,433
<i> No. You go ahead.</i>

334
00:19:47,567 --> 00:19:50,133
<i>Son, you need to go, please.
Go now.</i>

335
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:51,800
<i>- Dad, come on! Let's go!
- No.</i>

336
00:19:51,967 --> 00:19:53,300
<i> No, you go first. Go on.</i>

337
00:19:53,467 --> 00:19:55,200
<i>- Come on. You go first.
- But--</i>

338
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:57,433
<i>We've got this.
Go.</i>

339
00:19:57,567 --> 00:19:59,733
<i>- Dad, come on!
- Be careful, please.</i>

340
00:19:59,833 --> 00:20:00,900
<i> Go.</i>

341
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:02,533
<i> - Go ahead.</i> [CAR DOOR CLOSES]
- Dad!

342
00:20:02,667 --> 00:20:03,800
<i> Go home!</i>

343
00:20:06,833 --> 00:20:09,467
[ENGINE STARTS]

344
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,167
<i> Come on.</i>

345
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:22,300
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

346
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:27,500
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

347
00:20:27,633 --> 00:20:29,433
[SNIFFLES, BREATHES DEEPLY]

348
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:51,300
[CAR ENGINE HUMMING IN DISTANCE]

349
00:20:52,900 --> 00:20:54,333
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

350
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:57,700
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

351
00:20:59,567 --> 00:21:01,167
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

352
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:04,367
<i> Dad.</i>

353
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:06,467
<i> Who was that?</i>

354
00:21:11,533 --> 00:21:12,467
<i> Dad!</i>

355
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:16,333
<i> Dad, who was that?</i>

356
00:21:19,433 --> 00:21:21,300
<i>Is he an enemy of
you and Uncle Mike?</i>

357
00:21:24,333 --> 00:21:25,700
<i> Why did he hurt you?</i>

358
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,333
<i> Dad.</i>

359
00:21:32,233 --> 00:21:34,167
<i>- Dad, talk to me!
- Look.</i>

360
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:35,833
<i>You don't have to worry
about anything.</i>

361
00:21:37,867 --> 00:21:39,833
<i>Uncle Mike and I
have everything sorted out.</i>

362
00:21:42,033 --> 00:21:43,267
<i> Leon.</i>

363
00:21:44,233 --> 00:21:45,400
<i> Please remember,</i>

364
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:47,867
<i> this never happened.</i>

365
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:51,367
<i> Okay? This never happened.</i>

366
00:21:51,533 --> 00:21:58,667
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

367
00:22:01,867 --> 00:22:03,500
<i> Never happened?</i>

368
00:22:04,567 --> 00:22:05,900
<i> Dad, I killed someone!</i>

369
00:22:06,067 --> 00:22:07,233
<i> No, you didn't!</i>

370
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:14,367
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

371
00:22:15,267 --> 00:22:16,133
<i> I saw him.</i>

372
00:22:16,267 --> 00:22:17,800
<i> Look. Look. Look.</i>

373
00:22:17,933 --> 00:22:19,033
<i> Leon.</i>

374
00:22:19,133 --> 00:22:20,367
<i> Listen to me.</i>

375
00:22:21,967 --> 00:22:23,300
<i> This can ruin you.</i>

376
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:26,533
<i>If you let your emotions
take over,</i>

377
00:22:26,633 --> 00:22:28,933
<i>your mom will be affected,
as well as your siblings.</i>

378
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:33,267
<i> We're doing this for them.</i>

379
00:22:33,433 --> 00:22:34,867
<i> I'm doing this for you.</i>

380
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:39,267
<i> You didn't kill him.</i>

381
00:22:39,433 --> 00:22:40,400
<i> You didn't kill anyone.</i>

382
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:42,200
<i>That's on me.
Uncle Mike and I got this.</i>

383
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:43,900
<i> This is on us.</i>

384
00:22:47,100 --> 00:22:48,733
<i> Can you please promise me?</i>

385
00:22:52,367 --> 00:22:53,733
<i> Leon, please?</i>

386
00:22:54,967 --> 00:22:56,300
<i> Can you promise me?</i>

387
00:22:58,967 --> 00:22:59,900
<i> Please?</i>

388
00:23:01,433 --> 00:23:02,667
<i> This didn't happen.</i>

389
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:05,567
<i> Okay? This didn't happen.</i>

390
00:23:06,933 --> 00:23:08,733
<i>Let's just talk
about it again later, okay?</i>

391
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:10,767
<i> Please?</i>

392
00:23:12,833 --> 00:23:13,567
<i> Dad.</i>

393
00:23:13,667 --> 00:23:14,900
[FEDERICO] Promise me.

394
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:19,767
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

395
00:23:19,933 --> 00:23:21,300
<i> Is he dead?</i>

396
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:22,633
[SNIFFLES]

397
00:23:24,633 --> 00:23:29,867
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

398
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:30,933
<i> Look.</i>

399
00:23:32,500 --> 00:23:34,133
<i> I'll be gone for a few days.</i>

400
00:23:35,833 --> 00:23:38,700
<i>Your mommy and siblings
can't see me like this.</i>

401
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:41,967
<i>You know,
just tell them I have a...</i>

402
00:23:42,133 --> 00:23:44,633
<i>I have an
emergency business meeting.</i>

403
00:23:44,733 --> 00:23:46,800
<i> Look after them, okay?</i>

404
00:23:49,367 --> 00:23:50,467
<i> Come on, son.</i>

405
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:52,833
<i> I'll be back soon.</i>

406
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,333
<i> Okay?</i>

407
00:23:57,367 --> 00:23:58,567
<i> I love you, son.</i>

408
00:23:59,567 --> 00:24:00,733
[LEON SNIFFLES]

409
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:06,667
<i> I love you, son.</i>

410
00:24:06,833 --> 00:24:08,133
<i> Take care.</i>

411
00:24:08,233 --> 00:24:09,133
<i> I love you, Dad.</i>

412
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,333
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

413
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:14,367
[CAR ENGINE STARTS]

414
00:24:14,533 --> 00:24:21,367
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

415
00:24:21,533 --> 00:24:27,633
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

416
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:30,433
<i> It's impossible that
</i>what happened has nothing to do

417
00:24:30,567 --> 00:24:32,067
with Dad and Uncle Mike's death.

418
00:24:34,433 --> 00:24:36,100
<i> But the man is dead.</i>

419
00:24:36,233 --> 00:24:37,667
<i> I've killed him.</i>

420
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:47,200
<i>Did anyone know that
we were responsible for it?</i>

421
00:24:47,867 --> 00:24:49,200
<i> Does he have an accomplice?</i>

422
00:24:50,133 --> 00:24:52,100
<i>Does he have family
who wants to avenge him?</i>

423
00:24:55,133 --> 00:24:56,733
<i> If what Roi says is true...</i>

424
00:24:56,900 --> 00:24:57,700
<i> Bang! Bang!</i>

425
00:24:57,867 --> 00:24:59,200
[LEON]<i> That someone else
</i> murdered them,

426
00:24:59,367 --> 00:25:01,200
and that person is still free...

427
00:25:01,300 --> 00:25:02,567
<i> They didn't kill each other.</i>

428
00:25:03,433 --> 00:25:04,633
<i> There's someone else.</i>

429
00:25:06,333 --> 00:25:08,700
My siblings could be in danger.

430
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:11,600
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

431
00:25:11,767 --> 00:25:13,800
<i> I need to protect them.</i>

432
00:25:15,767 --> 00:25:22,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

433
00:25:33,067 --> 00:25:34,967
"Papa: I'll go to Belina.
I have a meeting there."

434
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:37,467
"Like I told you, anything for
our mission. Take care always."

435
00:25:40,533 --> 00:25:42,100
"Juan: Okay, Pa.
For our mission."

436
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:44,133
"Pa, pick up the phone.
Did you see something?"

437
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:46,067
"Papa? Where are you, Pa?"

438
00:25:47,333 --> 00:25:48,767
<i> Where are you, Pa?</i>

439
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:53,767
<i>I hope nothing bad
happened to you.</i>

440
00:25:54,633 --> 00:25:56,767
<i> But while I'm waiting,</i>

441
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:01,633
<i> I will continue our mission.</i>

442
00:26:02,433 --> 00:26:04,400
<i> I'll search for the treasure.</i>

443
00:26:04,500 --> 00:26:07,600
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

444
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:10,633
<i>- I didn't mean it.
- I'm sorry, sir.</i>

445
00:26:10,833 --> 00:26:12,633
<i>A knife?
Why does he have a knife?</i>

446
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:13,967
<i> Now that the truth is out,</i>

447
00:26:14,067 --> 00:26:15,633
<i>how will it be
with the Almazans?</i>

448
00:26:15,733 --> 00:26:17,467
<i>We need
to reconcile with them.</i>

449
00:26:17,633 --> 00:26:19,100
<i> Propose to me first.</i>

450
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:20,800
<i>- Propose?
- Yes.</i>

451
00:26:20,900 --> 00:26:23,133
It's not like everything's okay
<i> once we're at the hotel.</i>

452
00:26:23,233 --> 00:26:25,133
<i>As if they didn't say
anything bad about us.</i>

453
00:26:25,300 --> 00:26:27,533
I'm hoping that before I leave,

454
00:26:27,667 --> 00:26:30,133
<i> our families reconcile.</i>

455
00:26:30,233 --> 00:26:32,533
<i> Maybe it's time to revive</i>

456
00:26:32,667 --> 00:26:35,667
<i>the annual Hotel 88
team building!</i>

457
00:26:35,833 --> 00:26:38,267
<i>- Team building! Team--
- Sari.</i>

458
00:26:38,367 --> 00:26:39,367
<i> You are invited to join.</i>

459
00:26:39,500 --> 00:26:41,500
<i> Will Kiko be there?</i>

